<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8"?>
<html lang="en">
  <head>
    <title>Saxon-JS 2.4 XPath 3.1 and iXML fiddle</title>
  </head>
  <body>
    <section>
      <h1>Release 1.2.4.0.1 of Saxon-JS 2 XSLT 3 and Invisible XML Fiddle</h1>
      <section>
        <h2>Features</h2>
        <ul>
          <li>XPath 3.1 using Saxon-JS 2.4</li>
          <li>
            XPath execution using Saxon-JS 2.4
          </li>
          <li>now with load buttons to load input XML or JSON or HTML and/or XPath from local file system</li>
          <li>also save link/button to save result document to the file system</li>
          <li>save XML or JSON or HTML input and XPath code in URL query string</li>
          <li>experimental support for <a href="https://invisiblexml.org/">Invisible XML</a> using John Lumley's <a href="https://github.com/johnlumley/jwiXML">jwiXML library</a></li>
        </ul>
        <h3>Invisible XML example</h3>
        <section>
          <h4>Grammar</h4>
          <pre><code id="grammar1">Countries = Country*.
Country = Name, -'/', Code, -'/', Line, #A?.
Name = ['A'-'Z'],['A'-'Z'].
Code = ['0'-'9'],['0'-'9'],['0'-'9'].
Line = ['0'-'9'],['0'-'9'].
            </code>
          </pre>
          <h4>Sample data</h4>
          <pre><code id="data">UK/006/10
US/004/12</code></pre>
        </section>
      </section>
    </section>
  </body>
</html>
